 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Distributionally Adversarial Attack Framework\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook demonstrates how distributional analysis of bank transaction data can reveal privacy risks without accessing sensitive information."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "\n",
    "# Set style for better plots\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-v0_8')\n",
    "sns.set_palette(\"husl\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Import our attack components\n",
    "from src.attack_framework import PrivacyAttack\n",
    "from src.transaction_parser import TransactionParser\n",
    "from src.analysis_utils import AnalysisUtils"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Generate Sample Transaction Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Generate sample data\n",
    "parser = TransactionParser()\n",
    "sample_data = parser.generate_sample_data(150)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Generated {len(sample_data)} transactions for 5 accounts\")\n",
    "sample_data.head(10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Basic Data Exploration"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Basic statistics\n",
    "print(\"Transaction Data Summary:\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total transactions: {len(sample_data)}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Number of accounts: {sample_data['accountId'].nunique()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Date range: {sample_data['date'].min()} to {sample_data['date'].max()}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Average transaction amount: ${sample_data['amount'].mean():.2f}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Total spending: ${sample_data['amount'].sum():.2f}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Distribution of transaction amounts\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)\n",
    "plt.hist(sample_data['amount'], bins=30, alpha=0.7)\n",
    "plt.title('Distribution of Transaction Amounts')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Amount ($)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "\n",
    "# Category distribution\n",
    "plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)\n",
    "category_counts = sample_data['category'].value_counts()\n",
    "plt.pie(category_counts.values, labels=category_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')\n",
    "plt.title('Transaction Categories')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Privacy Attack Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Initialize attack framework\n",
    "attack = PrivacyAttack(sample_data)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Run the attack\n",
    "print(\"Running privacy attack analysis...\")\n",
    "results = attack.attack()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Attack completed successfully!\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Account Similarity Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Show account similarities\n",
    "print(\"Top 10 Account Similarities:\")\n",
    "for i, sim in enumerate(results['account_similarities'][:10]):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i+1}. Account {sim['account1']} <-> Account {sim['account2']}: {sim['similarity']:.3f}\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot similarity distribution\n",
    "similarities = [sim['similarity'] for sim in results['account_similarities']]\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))\n",
    "plt.hist(similarities, bins=20, alpha=0.7)\n",
    "plt.title('Distribution of Account Similarities')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Similarity Score')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Number of Account Pairs')\n",
    "plt.axvline(np.mean(similarities), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Mean: {np.mean(similarities):.3f}')\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Privacy Risk Assessment"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Show privacy risks\n",
    "print(\"Detected Privacy Risks:\")\n",
    "if results['privacy_risks']:\n",
    "    for risk in results['privacy_risks']:\n",
    "        print(f\"• {risk['risk_type']}: {risk['description']}\")\n",
    "        print(f\"  Details: {risk['details']}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"No significant privacy risks detected\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 4. Distributional Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Analyze distribution statistics by account\n",
    "account_groups = sample_data.groupby('accountId')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(15, 10))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Plot transaction amount distributions for each account\n",
    "for i, (account_id, group) in enumerate(account_groups):\n",
    "    plt.subplot(3, 2, i+1)\n",
    "    plt.hist(group['amount'], bins=15, alpha=0.7)\n",
    "    plt.title(f'Account {account_id} Distribution')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('Amount ($)')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Frequency')\n",
    "    \n",
    "plt.tight_layout()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Calculate and compare distributions between accounts\n",
    "account_stats = []\n",
    "for account_id, group in account_groups:\n",
    "    stats = AnalysisUtils.calculate_distribution_stats(group['amount'])\n",
    "    stats['accountId'] = account_id\n",
    "    account_stats.append(stats)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Account Distribution Statistics:\")\n",
    "stats_df = pd.DataFrame(account_stats)\n",
    "stats_df = stats_df[['accountId', 'mean', 'median', 'std', 'min', 'max', 'skewness', 'kurtosis']]\n",
    "stats_df"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 5. Key Findings and Implications"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Summary of Attack Findings\n",
    "\n",
    "This demonstration shows that even without accessing actual sensitive account information, distributional analysis of transaction patterns can reveal:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Account Similarity Patterns**: Accounts with similar spending behaviors can be identified\n",
    "2. **Spending Habit Inference**: Through statistical analysis of transaction distributions\n",
    "3. **Privacy Risk Identification**: Based on the distinguishability of different account patterns\n",
    "\n",
    "### Privacy Implications\n",
\n",
    "This type of attack demonstrates how distributional analysis can potentially\n",
    "reconstruct user privacy patterns without accessing sensitive data directly.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Educational Value\n",
    "\n",
    "This framework is designed to illustrate privacy risks in transaction data analysis\n",
    "without exposing real customer information."
   ]
  }
 ],
